abstract: The latest penalties against Iran were announced at a State Department forum condemning Tehran’s crackdown on human rights and religious freedoms.
snippet: The latest penalties against Iran were announced at a State Department forum condemning Tehran’s crackdown on human rights and religious freedoms.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — An Iranian judge who sentenced the American graduate student Xiyue Wang to a decade in prison was hit with United States sanctions on Thursday in the Trump administration’s latest pressure offensive against Tehran.

abstract: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo has a new deputy, assuring a degree of continuity at the helm of U.S. diplomacy should he resign for a potential Senate bid.
snippet: Secretary of State Mike Pompeo has a new deputy, assuring a degree of continuity at the helm of U.S. diplomacy should he resign for a potential Senate bid.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Secretary of State Mike Pompeo has a new deputy, assuring a degree of continuity at the helm of U.S. diplomacy should he resign for a potential Senate bid.
headline_main: Pompeo Gets a New Deputy Amid Speculation of a Senate Run
headline_print_headline: Pompeo Gets a New Deputy Amid Speculation of a Senate Run

abstract: Evidence is mounting that the bomb plot that killed the journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia reached deep into the government and business elite.
snippet: Evidence is mounting that the bomb plot that killed the journalist Daphne Caruana Galizia reached deep into the government and business elite.
lead_paragraph: VALLETTA, Malta — Soon after a car bomb killed Malta’s best-known journalist, Daphne Caruana Galizia, two years ago, the prime minister’s chief of staff had a hot tip for reporters covering the murder: It was a mafia hit by an Italian fuel-smuggling racket.

abstract: In passing the House, President Trump’s revised trade deal overcame the biggest remaining hurdle to becoming law.
snippet: In passing the House, President Trump’s revised trade deal overcame the biggest remaining hurdle to becoming law.
lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The House overwhelmingly approved a revised North American trade pact by a vote of 385 to 41 on Thursday, giving President Trump and the Democratic majority an improbable bipartisan victory less than 24 hours after Mr. Trump was impeached for high crimes and misdemeanors.

abstract: Nuclear industry hopes of one day bringing small, factory-built nuclear power plants to communities and industrial sites have cleared a first regulatory hurdle with the Trump administration, over objections from the Federal Emergency Management Agency and others that regulators are cutting corners on safety and disaster planning.

lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — Nuclear industry hopes of one day bringing small, factory-built nuclear power plants to communities and industrial sites have cleared a first regulatory hurdle with the Trump administration, over objections from the Federal Emergency Management Agency and others that regulators are cutting corners on safety and disaster planning.
headline_main: NRC Gives Permit for Next-Gen Factory-Built Nuclear Reactor
headline_print_headline: NRC Gives Permit for Next-Gen Factory-Built Nuclear Reactor

abstract: President Trump is expected to sign it into law as part of the overall spending package. Some advocates warn that more action is needed to reduce teenage vaping of e-cigarettes.
snippet: President Trump is expected to sign it into law as part of the overall spending package. Some advocates warn that more action is needed to reduce teenage vaping of e-cigarettes.
lead_paragraph: The House and Senate have now passed a provision that would ban the sale of tobacco and e-cigarettes to anyone under 21, at a time when Congress and the Trump administration are facing public pressure to reduce the soaring rates of teenage vaping.

abstract: With humor and fantasy, Kent Monkman disrupts clichés of Native victimhood at the Met.
snippet: With humor and fantasy, Kent Monkman disrupts clichés of Native victimhood at the Met.
lead_paragraph: Coonskin caps for Christmas! I was a kid in mid-20th-century America. The biggest cultural event I can remember from early childhood was Walt Disney’s gigantically popular “Davy Crockett: Indian Fighter” on TV. The first installment of a serial, which debuted on Dec. 15, 1954, it was basically about the exploits of a Tennessee backwoods gun-for-hire, and promoted nostalgia for the days when the Wild West was “won” from indigenous peoples. A verse of the theme song, which was everywhere on the radio, went:
